LUMPY SKIN DISEASE - ASIA (03): INDONESIA (RIAU) CATTLE, OIE, FIRST REPORT
**************************************************************************
A ProMED-mail post
http://www.promedmail.org
ProMED-mail is a program of the
International Society for Infectious Diseases
http://www.isid.org

[1] OIE-WAHIS: immediate notification
Date: Wed 2 Mar 2022
Source: OIE-WAHIS (World Animal Health Information System) 2022 [abridged, edited]
https://wahis.oie.int/#/report-info?reportId=49767


Lumpy skin disease was detected in cattle in Rengat, Indragiri Hulu, Riau on 7 Feb 2022. A total of 31 outbreaks (submitted) have been reported to date [4 Mar 2022].

Affected population: Riau province has 12 districts. The 1st case was reported in Indragiri Hulu District. Up to 2 Mar 2022, 174 cases have been reported in 31 villages in 5 districts.

Epidemiological comments: Since 7 Feb 2022, the distribution of the disease is as follows: Bengkalis District 4 cases in 2 villages, Dumai District 6 cases in 2 villages, Indragiri Hilir District 17 cases in 1 village, Indragiri Hulu District 104 cases in 14 villages, Kampar District 22 Cases in 3 villages, Pelalawan District 2 cases in 2 villages, Siak District 19 cases in 7 villages. Animal movement and vector is suspected to be the risk factor for the disease spread. Vaccination is not yet implemented and will be the main intervention to control the disease.

[The locations of the outbreaks can be seen on the interactive map included in the OIE report at the source URL above.]

