[ProMED thanks Mahmoud Orabi for his submission.

LSD has spread since 2019 into the following Asian/South-East Asian countries: Bangladesh, India, China, Bhutan, Nepal, Viet Nam, Taiwan, Myanmar, China (Hong Kong SAR), Sri Lanka, Thailand, Cambodia, Malaysia, Lao's People Democratic Republic and Mongolia. Its introduction into Sumatra is indeed a cause for grave concern in Australia, as adequately addressed in Dr Ainsworth's article.

The following background PPTs are suggested for further reading:
